Opener’s first and most important responsibility after a raise is to reevaluate her hand and decide how much 
it’s really worth. 
When responder is able to raise directly (either ...2,3, or 4 of your major, or a Bergen raise, splinter, or Jacoby 2NT) 
opener can frequently place the contract immediately. 
This lesson addresses 2 items -- hand reevaluation and final contract placement. 
The section on evaluation is taken from Marty Bergen’s book, “Slam Bidding Made Easy”.|
