^*BRe-evaluation after a raise:^*N 

If pard raises your opening bid of 1@H or 1@S, you are likely to declare the hand 
(assuming your side buys the contract, of course). 
Here are Bergen’s  guidelines for calculating your hand’s strength after a raise: |
pg| ***** 14 ***** |


at|

a) Start with initial evaluation (= starting points)
b) If you have 2 doubletons, add 1 point (don’t add anything for just one doubleton)
c) Add 2 points for a singleton
d) Add 4 points for a void.
e) Add 1 point for the each trump over 5 (1 point for 6 card suit, 2 for 7-card suit, etc)
f) Add 1 point for an outside 4 card suit. |
